WEBVTT

00:01.709 --> 00:03.500
Charlie: <i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:03.583 --> 00:05.125
YOU'RE HIM.
YOU'RE CHARLIE'S DAD.

00:05.208 --> 00:06.583
<i>MY DAD WAS WITH ME</i>
<i>WHEN I HAD MY ACCIDENT,</i>

00:06.667 --> 00:07.959
<i>AND HE LOST</i>
<i>HIS VISITATION RIGHTS.</i>

00:08.041 --> 00:09.625
IT'S REALLY COMPLICATED.

00:09.709 --> 00:11.041
NO ONE DESERVES
TO BE PITIED.

00:11.125 --> 00:12.667
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND THAT
BECAUSE --

00:12.750 --> 00:14.041
WELL,
NO ONE PITIES YOU, EMMA.

00:14.125 --> 00:15.625
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE
IN THIS HOSPITAL.

00:15.709 --> 00:17.667
SPEAKING OF LEO --
OR EMMA AND LEO --

00:17.750 --> 00:19.041
HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT
THAT WHOLE SITCH, MAN?

00:19.125 --> 00:20.250
MY LIFE IS WEIRDLY STABLE

00:20.333 --> 00:21.333
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN FOREVER.

00:21.417 --> 00:22.792
MY MOM'S AROUND.

00:22.875 --> 00:24.083
I'M NOT ABOUT TO RUIN THAT
OVER A GIRL.

00:24.166 --> 00:25.625
JORDI'S MOM LEFT LAST NIGHT.

00:25.709 --> 00:27.542
SHE IS RELINQUISHING
GUARDIANSHIP.

00:27.625 --> 00:28.834
HE'S OFFICIALLY ON HIS WAY

00:28.917 --> 00:30.250
TO BECOMING
AN EMANCIPATED MINOR.

00:30.333 --> 00:32.166
WHICH IS JUST A FANCY WORD
FOR ALONE.

00:34.208 --> 00:37.083
[ MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY ]

00:46.959 --> 00:48.208
[ SIGHS ]

00:48.291 --> 00:50.458
WHAT --
ARE WE HOUSING THE HOMELESS NOW?

00:55.417 --> 00:58.041
WHAT THE HELL IS YOUR STORY,
COMA BOY?

01:03.291 --> 01:06.333
<i>I'M SO GLAD YOU FINALLY ASKED.</i>

01:12.917 --> 01:14.417
<i>THIS IS ME THREE YEARS AGO.</i>

01:14.500 --> 01:16.458
<i>CHECK OUT</i>
<i>MY BRAIN-WAVE ACTIVITY, RIGHT?</i>

01:16.542 --> 01:18.917
<i>I'M OBSESSED WITH THIS GAME</i>
<i>THAT MY DAD MADE UP,</i>

01:19.000 --> 01:21.166
<i>"GAMIVERSE."</i>
SAY CHEESE.

01:21.250 --> 01:23.834
<i>I KNOW. HAPPY TIMES.</i>
<i>SNOOZEFEST.</i>

01:23.917 --> 01:25.709
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]
<i>LET'S GET TO THE GOOD STUFF.</i>

01:25.792 --> 01:27.333
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

01:27.417 --> 01:29.000
<i>THIS IS ME FOUR MONTHS AGO,</i>

01:29.083 --> 01:31.417
<i>A.K.A. THE NIGHT</i>
<i>EVERYTHING WENT DARK.</i>

01:31.500 --> 01:32.875
[ SIGHS ]
HE'S FINE, BABE.

01:32.959 --> 01:34.375
ARE YOU SEEING THE LEVEL

01:34.458 --> 01:36.125
OF SUGAR INTAKE
THAT'S GOING ON OVER THERE?

01:36.208 --> 01:38.959
HE'S GONNA BE WIRED
ALL NIGHT.
HE'S HAVING FUN.

01:39.041 --> 01:41.417
<i>YOU'RE</i> HAVING FUN.
HE SHOULD BE ASLEEP IN AN HOUR,

01:41.500 --> 01:43.000
AND SINCE I'M THE ONE

01:43.083 --> 01:44.542
WHO HAS TO GET UP WITH HIM
IN THE MORNING --

01:44.625 --> 01:46.000
ONLY BECAUSE I'VE GOT TO BE
AT WORK EARLY.

01:46.083 --> 01:49.000
I'M SURE SUSAN
CAN DRIVE ME HOME.

01:49.083 --> 01:51.542
YEAH. THAT'S FINE.

01:51.625 --> 01:54.500
Charlie: DAD! OH, WE HAVE TO
GET THIS GAME, OKAY?

01:54.583 --> 01:56.750
UH, UH, THERE'S THESE ALIENS,
AND YOU, LIKE, BLAST THEM,

01:56.834 --> 01:58.291
AND THEIR GUTS
ARE ALL NASTY,

01:58.375 --> 01:59.834
BUT IT'S NOT VIOLENT.
I SWEAR.

01:59.917 --> 02:01.208
WE'LL SEE, BUDDY.
COME ON.

02:01.291 --> 02:02.709
WE'RE GONNA MEET MOM
AT HOME.

02:02.792 --> 02:05.291
WAIT. WE'RE LEAVING ALREADY?
WHY?

02:05.375 --> 02:06.834
'CAUSE I'M THE GROWN-UP,
AND I SAY SO. THAT'S WHY.

02:06.917 --> 02:10.333
<i>GROWN-UPS ARE SUCH BUZZ KILLS.</i>

02:10.417 --> 02:12.583
<i>EXHIBIT "A" --</i>
<i>JORDI'S SOCIAL WORKER.</i>

02:12.667 --> 02:14.458
THERE ARE SOME ASPECTS
OF ADULTHOOD

02:14.542 --> 02:16.875
THAT MAY BE DAUNTING
AND SOMEWHAT DISAPPOINTING.

02:16.959 --> 02:19.792
A LOT OF KIDS IN YOUR POSITION
THINK THAT GROWING UP IS "COOL."

02:19.875 --> 02:21.834
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ Chuckling ] YEAH.

02:21.917 --> 02:24.375
YEAH, WE'RE ROLLING LIKE
PHARRELL UP IN HERE.

02:24.458 --> 02:25.792
WHAT I MEAN TO SAY IS,

02:25.875 --> 02:28.083
EMANCIPATION SEEMS LIKE
AN APPEALING OPTION,

02:28.166 --> 02:29.875
BUT IT IS MY JOB
TO MAKE YOU AWARE

02:29.959 --> 02:31.375
OF YOUR
RESPONSIBILITIES --

02:31.458 --> 02:33.458
THINGS THAT YOUR PARENTS
ALWAYS DEALT WITH,

02:33.542 --> 02:36.125
LIKE FILING TAX RETURNS OR
KEEPING A CLEAN CREDIT HISTORY.

02:36.208 --> 02:38.166
YEAH, I'M PRETTY SURE MY MOM
NEVER DID ANY OF THAT STUFF.

02:38.250 --> 02:41.500
HEY, YOU CAN GET A CREDIT CARD.
THAT'S KIND OF COOL.

02:41.583 --> 02:43.709
IT <i>IS</i> GOOD
TO ESTABLISH CREDIT,

02:43.792 --> 02:45.375
BUT IT CAN ALSO LEAD
TO A MOUNTAIN OF DEBT,

02:45.458 --> 02:47.375
WHICH WOULD BE BAD.
WELL, WHAT KIND OF DEBT

02:47.458 --> 02:49.291
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT, EXACTLY?
DO YOU MEAN

02:49.375 --> 02:51.917
THE BILLIONS OF DOLLARS OF DEBT
THE FED IS SELLING EVERY DAY

02:52.000 --> 02:53.792
AT ABSURDLY LOW RATES
TO KEEP OUR ECONOMY
ARTIFICIALLY AFLOAT,

02:53.875 --> 02:56.375
OR ARE YOU REFERRING TO MORE OF
A PERSONAL KIND OF DEBT?

02:56.458 --> 02:58.041
IN WHICH CASE,
A GOOD RULE OF THUMB

02:58.125 --> 02:59.834
IS YOUR TOTAL
MONTHLY DEBT PAYMENTS

02:59.917 --> 03:02.083
SHOULDN'T EXCEED 15% TO 20%
OF YOUR TAKE-HOME INCOME.

03:05.875 --> 03:08.333
I'D BE HAPPY TO SET YOU UP
IN ANY NUMBER OF GROUP HOMES

03:08.417 --> 03:10.250
WITH MINORS
IN SIMILAR SITUATIONS.

03:10.333 --> 03:12.333
I DON'T NEED A HOME.

03:12.417 --> 03:13.917
I HAVE PEOPLE
WHO CARE ABOUT ME.

03:14.000 --> 03:15.875
UNFORTUNATELY,
THOSE SAME PEOPLE ALSO BELIEVE

03:15.959 --> 03:17.750
THAT CANCER CAN BE CURED
BY FARM ANIMALS,

03:17.834 --> 03:19.875
SO AS FAR AS
MY MEDICAL DECISIONS GO,

03:19.959 --> 03:21.709
I HAVE TO BE IN CHARGE.

03:21.792 --> 03:23.583
I NEED TO DO THIS MYSELF.

03:23.667 --> 03:25.667
WHAT ELSE?

03:25.750 --> 03:28.542
Dash: MR. COBB, GLAD TO FINALLY
GET YOU ON THE LINE.

03:28.625 --> 03:30.125
[ SNIFFS ]

03:30.208 --> 03:32.750
OH, NO. NO FAULT OF GLORIA'S,
SIR. SHE'S A PEACH.

03:32.834 --> 03:35.667
BUT I WAS HOPING TO HAVE
A MEETING AT YOUR HOME OFFICE.

03:35.750 --> 03:38.333
YOU'RE STILL ON 10504
WILSHIRE BOULEVARD, CORRECT?

03:38.417 --> 03:41.041
DASH. I'VE BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER FOR YOU.

03:41.125 --> 03:42.834
AH, MY ASSOCIATE
JUST WALKED IN.

03:42.917 --> 03:45.500
GONNA HAVE TO CALL YOU BACK.

03:45.583 --> 03:46.792
WHAT'S UP, DOC?

03:46.875 --> 03:48.125
I GOT GREAT NEWS.

03:48.208 --> 03:50.291
YOU'RE GETTING YOUR PAGER.

03:50.375 --> 03:51.709
A PAGER?
[ SCOFFS ]

03:51.792 --> 03:53.125
WHAT IS HE --
A PIMP FROM THE '90s?

03:53.208 --> 03:55.000
DOES NOT CONCERN YOU, KARA.

03:55.083 --> 03:56.291
WELL, THEN, TALK QUIETER.

03:56.375 --> 03:58.500
SO I MOVED UP ON THE LIST?
YES.

03:58.583 --> 04:00.667
ONCE YOU'RE DONE WITH YOUR
TUNE-UP, YOU'RE GONNA GO HOME.

04:00.750 --> 04:02.208
YOU'RE GONNA WAIT
FOR THAT PAGER TO BEEP.

04:02.291 --> 04:03.667
AND WHEN IT DOES,
YOU COME BACK HERE,

04:03.750 --> 04:05.333
AND WE ARE
OFF TO THE RACES.

04:05.417 --> 04:07.709
I WAS THINKING YOU WAS JUST
GONNA COME IN HERE

04:07.792 --> 04:10.000
AND TELL ME THERE WAS
BUTTERSCOTCH PUDDING TODAY.

04:10.083 --> 04:12.166
BUT YOU CAME IN HERE
ON A WHOLE OTHER LEVEL.

04:12.250 --> 04:14.417
IT'S WHAT I DO.

04:14.500 --> 04:16.291
CONGRATS.

04:18.834 --> 04:21.041
SO, UH, WHAT'S A TUNE-UP?

04:21.125 --> 04:23.166
IS IT LIKE A NIP/TUCK?

04:23.250 --> 04:26.000
YOU HAVE DRY-ERASE FACE.

04:26.083 --> 04:28.375
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT KIND OF LIST ARE YOU ON?

04:28.458 --> 04:31.250
ORGAN DONOR, THE ONLY LIST
THAT MATTERS IN HERE.

04:31.333 --> 04:32.917
WHAT DO YOU NEED
AN ORGAN FOR?

04:33.000 --> 04:35.375
DON'T YOU HAVE, LIKE,
CYSTIC ACNE OR SOMETHING?

04:35.458 --> 04:37.208
[ SIGHS ] NOPE.

04:37.291 --> 04:38.792
NOT HAVING
THIS CONVERSATION.

04:48.125 --> 04:50.041
OH. HEY!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

04:50.125 --> 04:52.375
TODAY'S NOT ONE OF YOUR DAYS,
JAMES TAYLOR.

04:52.458 --> 04:54.959
NOT ONCE HAVE I PLAYED
A JAMES TAYLOR SONG.

04:55.041 --> 04:56.417
I'M JUST NUDGING YOU
TOWARDS

04:56.500 --> 04:58.041
WHAT I THINK MIGHT BE
YOUR COMFORT ZONE.

04:58.125 --> 04:59.709
UH, NOW, LISTEN,
YOU NEED TO GO HOME NOW.

04:59.792 --> 05:02.125
I CAN'T BE HERE TOMORROW.
MY SHIFTS CHANGED.

05:02.208 --> 05:04.208
DOES IT REALLY MATTER?
OF COURSE IT MATTERS.

05:04.291 --> 05:05.750
I KEEP TABS
ON WHO GOES WHERE WHEN

05:05.834 --> 05:07.125
BECAUSE THERE'S ALWAYS
A WHY.

05:07.208 --> 05:08.291
UNDERSTOOD?

05:09.375 --> 05:11.000
MANDY IS HERE.

05:12.166 --> 05:13.333
WHY?
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

05:13.417 --> 05:15.083
S-SHE'S SUPPOSED TO BE
WORKING TODAY.

05:15.166 --> 05:16.834
YES, SHE IS, ISN'T SHE?

05:16.917 --> 05:19.125
NORMALLY, MANDY WORKS
TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY,

05:19.208 --> 05:21.709
AND HER GRAVEYARD SHIFTS
ARE FRIDAY, SATURDAY, SUNDAY,

05:21.792 --> 05:23.208
WITH ALTERNATING
MONDAYS OFF.

05:23.291 --> 05:24.875
I KNOW THESE THINGS
FOR A REASON.

05:24.959 --> 05:26.000
NOW GET YOUR ASS HOME.

05:27.625 --> 05:30.250
THEY'RE COMING TODAY...
AREN'T THEY?

05:30.333 --> 05:32.250
<i>WHO'S "THEY"?</i>

05:32.333 --> 05:34.959
<i>OH, THEM. CRAP.</i>

05:35.041 --> 05:37.583
I'LL CALL YOU
WHEN IT'S SAFE TO COME BACK.

05:37.667 --> 05:39.041
I PROMISE.

05:44.709 --> 05:45.834
WHAT'S UP
WITH CHARLIE'S DAD?

05:45.917 --> 05:48.625
HOW DID --
I'M LATE FOR ROUNDS.

05:48.709 --> 05:50.792
WAIT.
WAS THAT TRAGIC WAITRESS

05:50.875 --> 05:53.458
WHO WAS CRASHING IN MY ROOM
LAST NIGHT

05:53.542 --> 05:55.083
SNOOZE DOGGY-DOG'S MOM?

05:55.166 --> 05:56.959
SHUT IT DOWN, KARA.
OKAY?

05:57.041 --> 05:59.667
TODAY IS NOT THE DAY.
YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

05:59.750 --> 06:02.792
AND WHY IS TODAY DIFFERENT
FROM ALL OTHER DAYS?

06:02.875 --> 06:05.333
MA NISHTANA-ZY?
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:06.834 --> 06:09.458
<i>AWESOME THING NUMBER 374</i>
<i>ABOUT NURSE JACKSON --</i>

06:09.542 --> 06:11.625
<i>NOT ONLY DOES SHE</i>
<i>LOOK OUT FOR ME,</i>

06:11.709 --> 06:13.125
<i>SHE LOOKS OUT FOR MY DAD.</i>

06:13.208 --> 06:16.667
[ SIGHS ]
GOOD MORNING, LITTLE MAN.

06:16.750 --> 06:18.792
HOW YOU FEELING TODAY?

06:18.875 --> 06:20.667
[ CHARLIE GROANS ]
NOT SO GOOD.

06:20.750 --> 06:23.125
I THINK I'M GONNA HURL.
WELL, THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS

06:23.208 --> 06:25.000
WHEN YOU CHASE
FOUR BOWLS OF ICE CREAM

06:25.083 --> 06:26.208
WITH THREE CANS OF SODA.

06:26.291 --> 06:28.041
JUST TAKE DEEP BREATHS.

06:30.583 --> 06:31.542
[ VOMITS ]

06:31.625 --> 06:32.625
[ COUGHING ]

06:32.709 --> 06:34.542
OH. BUDDY, HEY.

06:34.625 --> 06:35.750
YOU OKAY?

06:35.834 --> 06:37.834
[ SPITS ]
OHH, I'M SORRY, DAD.

06:37.917 --> 06:40.500
NO, IT'S OKAY.
JUST LIE DOWN IF YOU NEED TO.

06:40.583 --> 06:43.500
DAD, I-I CAN'T.
MY SEAT BELT -- I-I-IT'S STUCK.

06:43.583 --> 06:45.834
OKAY.

06:45.917 --> 06:48.709
WE'RE -- WE'RE --
WE'RE ALMOST HOME, OKAY?

06:48.792 --> 06:50.041
ALMOST THERE.

06:50.125 --> 06:52.709
[ HORN BLARES,
TIRES SCREECHING ]

06:52.792 --> 06:56.458
[ CRASHING ]

06:56.542 --> 06:59.792
<i>LIKE I SAID,</i>
<i>EVERYTHING JUST WENT DARK.</i>

07:01.417 --> 07:04.417
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

07:19.041 --> 07:20.250
OH, MY GOSH.

07:20.333 --> 07:21.542
ARE YOU GUYS FBI?

07:23.041 --> 07:24.792
AM I BEING AUDITED?

07:24.875 --> 07:27.583
UH, GOOD MORNING.

07:27.667 --> 07:29.291
CAN I HELP YOU?

07:29.375 --> 07:31.792
JOHN FISHER. SEAN FAHEY. HERE
TO ASSESS CHARLIE HUTCHISON.

07:31.875 --> 07:34.291
[ <i>Singsong voice</i> ]
<i>THEY'RE BA-A-CK.</i>
OH, THAT MAKES MORE SENSE.

07:34.375 --> 07:35.709
RIGHT THIS WAY.

07:41.208 --> 07:43.333
HEY.

07:43.417 --> 07:45.667
<i>REMEMBER THIS?</i>

07:45.750 --> 07:47.625
<i>SO DOES EMMA.</i>

07:47.709 --> 07:49.041
EMMA.

07:49.125 --> 07:50.875
EMMA, WAIT UP.

07:50.959 --> 07:53.667
OH, EMMA! LEO!

07:53.750 --> 07:56.500
JUST THE PEOPLE
I'M LOOKING FOR.

07:56.583 --> 07:59.166
[ SIGHS ] FIRST EDITION
OF "MRS. DALLOWAY."

07:59.250 --> 08:01.166
I THOUGHT
YOU WOULD ENJOY.

08:01.250 --> 08:04.166
I WILL ENJOY IT,
BUT WHY ARE YOU GIVING IT TO ME?

08:04.250 --> 08:06.834
BECAUSE I CAN'T TAKE IT WITH ME
WHEN I GO.

08:06.917 --> 08:08.834
OH, MY GOD.
YOU'RE DYING?

08:08.917 --> 08:10.000
EVENTUALLY.

08:10.083 --> 08:12.000
BUT FOR NOW,
I AM GOING TO INDIA.

08:12.083 --> 08:13.542
I'VE HAD A VISION,
CHILDREN,

08:13.625 --> 08:15.333
OF THE "EAT, PRAY, LOVE"
VARIETY.

08:15.417 --> 08:18.000
I KNOW I'M LATE
TO THE ELIZABETH GILBERT PARTY,

08:18.083 --> 08:20.166
BUT, BOY, CAN THAT DAME
SPIN A YARN.

08:20.250 --> 08:21.542
STRAIGHT FROM WOODSTOCK.

08:21.625 --> 08:23.542
I-I CAN'T TAKE THIS.
I INSIST.

08:23.625 --> 08:27.667
I'M LEAVING EACH OF YOU
A SMALL TOKEN TO REMEMBER ME BY.

08:27.750 --> 08:29.166
NOW, WHERE IS JORDI?

08:29.250 --> 08:31.542
I HAVE A PUKA-SHELL NECKLACE
WITH HIS NAME ON IT.

08:31.625 --> 08:32.917
HE'S IN HIS ROOM,
BUT, UM,

08:33.000 --> 08:34.667
I'M NOT SURE
THAT NOW'S THE BEST TIME.

08:34.750 --> 08:36.417
HE'S GOT A SOCIAL WORKER
IN THERE WITH HIM

08:36.500 --> 08:39.667
TALKING ABOUT TAX RETURNS AND
ALL THIS OTHER GROWN-UP STUFF.

08:39.750 --> 08:41.542
FRANKLY,
THE WHOLE THING SUCKS.

08:41.625 --> 08:43.542
IT DOES SUCK.

08:43.625 --> 08:46.208
TO WILLINGLY
EMBRACE ADULTHOOD --

08:46.291 --> 08:47.583
NO SMALL THING.

08:50.125 --> 08:52.166
BUT...

08:52.250 --> 08:56.041
NOT EVERYTHING ABOUT
BEING A GROWN-UP HAS TO SUCK.

08:56.125 --> 08:59.083
YEAH, COME WITH ME.
WE'RE NOT DOING DRUGS NOW.

08:59.166 --> 09:02.917
NONETHELESS, COME WITH ME.

09:09.667 --> 09:11.041
WHAT DISEASE DO YOU HAVE

09:11.125 --> 09:12.834
THAT GETS YOU
ON AN ORGAN-DONOR LIST?

09:12.917 --> 09:14.709
'CAUSE IF WE'RE COMPETING
FOR HEARTS, I NEED TO KNOW.

09:14.792 --> 09:16.750
FIRST OF ALL,
IF WE WERE COMPETING

09:16.834 --> 09:18.417
FOR <i>ANYTHING,</i>
I WOULD WIN.

09:18.500 --> 09:21.625
LUCKILY FOR YOU,
I HAVE CYSTIC FIBROSIS.

09:21.709 --> 09:22.792
I NEED LUNGS.

09:22.875 --> 09:24.750
FOR WHAT?

09:24.834 --> 09:28.083
FOR THE SAME REASON
YOU NEED LUNGS...?

09:28.166 --> 09:29.500
I REPEAT, FOR WHAT?

09:29.583 --> 09:31.250
OKAY, SO, YOU KNOW
WHEN YOU'RE SCREAMING

09:31.333 --> 09:33.000
AT A CHEERLEADER
FOR KICKING TOO HIGH,

09:33.083 --> 09:35.542
AND SHE STARTS TO CRY, AND SNOT
STARTS TO RUN DOWN HER FACE,

09:35.625 --> 09:37.583
AND YOU COULD GET HER A KLEENEX,
BUT YOU DON'T,

09:37.667 --> 09:39.125
BECAUSE YOU DON'T
GIVE A CRAP?

09:39.208 --> 09:43.917
YEAH, SO, WITH ME, MY SNOT --
IT'S LIKE CONCRETE.

09:44.041 --> 09:45.792
IF IT GETS STUCK,
I CAN'T BREATHE.

09:45.875 --> 09:48.166
IF MY MUCUS DOESN'T MOVE,
I DROWN TO DEATH.

09:49.208 --> 09:50.542
RIGHT.

09:50.625 --> 09:52.917
SO, YOU'RE ON
THE ORGAN-DONOR LIST,

09:53.000 --> 09:56.166
TO WHICH I'M NOT INVITED,
WHICH IS REPREHENSIBLE.

09:56.250 --> 09:58.792
I MEAN [SCOFFS] I WALK TWO FEET
DOWN SUNSET BOULEVARD,

09:58.875 --> 10:01.583
AND I AUTOMATICALLY GET ON LISTS
THAT DON'T EVEN EXIST YET,

10:01.667 --> 10:03.000
BUT WHATEVS.

10:03.083 --> 10:05.625
THE POINT IS,
WHAT AM I DOING WRONG?

10:05.709 --> 10:07.458
YOU MUST KNOW SOMETHING.

10:07.542 --> 10:10.166
I KNOW LOTS OF THINGS.

10:10.250 --> 10:12.667
AND, CLEARLY,
<i>YOU</i> KNOW LOTS OF THINGS.

10:12.750 --> 10:13.959
MEANING WHAT?

10:14.041 --> 10:15.375
MEANING I COULD HELP YOU,

10:15.458 --> 10:17.667
BUT FIRST,
YOU'RE GONNA NEED TO HELP ME.

10:17.750 --> 10:20.959
FINE.
BUT YOU HAVE TO USE A CONDOM.

10:21.041 --> 10:22.542
[ SCOFFS, CHUCKLES ]

10:24.709 --> 10:26.375
THIS IS
A LIST OF RESIDENTS

10:26.458 --> 10:28.667
THAT LIVE AT
10504 WILSHIRE BOULEVARD.

10:28.750 --> 10:30.125
IT'S LUXURY CONDOMINIUMS.

10:30.208 --> 10:32.333
DO YOU KNOW
ANYONE ON THIS LIST?

10:32.417 --> 10:33.792
THAT DEPENDS.

10:33.875 --> 10:36.000
IS THIS, LIKE,
A GRASSY KNOLL SITUATION?

10:36.083 --> 10:38.000
I NEED TO
GET INTO THE BUILDING.

10:38.083 --> 10:41.166
IF YOU CAN GET ME IN, WE CAN
CONTINUE THIS CONVERSATION.

10:41.250 --> 10:42.625
SO THAT'S HOW THIS WORKS?

10:42.709 --> 10:44.542
THAT'S HOW IT WORKS.

10:44.625 --> 10:46.208
ARE THESE
HIS MOST RECENT LABS?

10:46.291 --> 10:47.542
UM,
THAT'S CORRECT.

10:47.625 --> 10:49.166
IF YOU LOOK
AT THURSDAY'S WORK,

10:49.250 --> 10:51.166
YOU'LL SEE HE HAD
SOME IMPRESSIVE SPIKES

10:51.250 --> 10:52.375
IN HIS BRAIN ACTIVITY.

10:52.458 --> 10:53.875
YES,
BUT SPIKES CAN BE RANDOM.

10:53.959 --> 10:55.667
<i>TECHNICALLY,</i>
<i>I WAS HAVING A DAYDREAM</i>

10:55.750 --> 10:57.709
<i>ABOUT ME AND SHAILENE WOODLEY</i>
<i>ON A JET SKI.</i>

10:57.792 --> 10:59.792
WE LOOK FOR CONSISTENCY
IN THE TESTING

10:59.875 --> 11:01.500
BEFORE MAKING ANY DECISIONS
WHETHER OR NOT

11:01.583 --> 11:03.333
TO TRANSFER HIM
TO A LONG-TERM-CARE FACILITY.

11:03.417 --> 11:06.333
<i>TRANSFERRED? WHY?</i>
<i>I'M INCREDIBLY LOW-MAINTENANCE.</i>

11:06.417 --> 11:09.709
I'M NOT SURE TRANSFERRING HIM
IS THE BEST IDEA RIGHT NOW.

11:09.792 --> 11:11.208
THERE'S A LOT
WE CAN STILL DO FOR CHARLIE.

11:11.291 --> 11:12.583
JUST LAST WEEK,
WE WERE DISCUSSING --

11:12.667 --> 11:14.208
WHAT WAS THAT TREATMENT
CALLED AGAIN?

11:14.291 --> 11:16.166
UH, WHAT -- WHAT NURSE JACKSON
IS TRYING TO SAY

11:16.250 --> 11:18.083
IS THAT WE --
WE REMAIN CONFIDENT.

11:18.166 --> 11:20.709
HE'S YOUNG. HE'S STRONG. HE HAS
NO PRE-EXISTING CONDITIONS.

11:20.792 --> 11:22.583
ALL OF WHICH WE'LL
TAKE INTO ACCOUNT IN OUR REVIEW.

11:22.667 --> 11:24.875
CAN YOU TELL US MORE
ABOUT THE EVENING

11:24.959 --> 11:26.375
THIS PATIENT WAS ADMITTED?

11:26.458 --> 11:28.750
UH, DR. POTTER
WAS HIS SURGEON, SO --

11:28.834 --> 11:29.959
BUT I WAS THERE.

11:31.125 --> 11:34.250
I WAS WORKING AN EXTRA SHIFT IN
THE E.R. WHEN CHARLIE CAME IN.

11:34.333 --> 11:36.583
<i>REMEMBER WHAT I WAS SAYING</i>
<i>ABOUT THAT DARK NIGHT?</i>

11:36.667 --> 11:38.208
WHAT HAVE WE GOT?
<i>IT GETS DARKER.</i>

11:38.291 --> 11:40.667
UNRESTRAINED PASSENGER,
AWAKE ON ARRIVAL AT THE SCENE.

11:40.750 --> 11:42.542
HEART RATE 150.
B.P. 110...

11:42.625 --> 11:44.375
I'M HIS FATHER.

11:44.458 --> 11:47.208
SIR, WE'RE GONNA NEED YOU
TO FINISH THE ACCIDENT REPORT.

11:47.291 --> 11:49.041
DAD?

11:49.125 --> 11:50.709
I'M NOT -- I'M NOT LEAVING YOU,
CHARLIE, OKAY?

11:50.792 --> 11:51.917
OH, THANK GOD.

11:52.000 --> 11:54.041
WHAT HAPPENED?
WHERE'S CHARLIE?

11:54.125 --> 11:56.959
ARE YOU OKAY, BABY?
MOM.

11:57.041 --> 11:59.542
THE PARAMEDIC MENTIONED
YOUR SON'S SEAT BELT?

11:59.625 --> 12:00.709
NICK?

12:02.500 --> 12:04.250
HE THREW UP
IN THE BACK SEAT.

12:04.333 --> 12:06.667
HE WAS SICK.
WE WERE ALMOST HOME.

12:09.208 --> 12:10.792
HE WASN'T
WEARING HIS SEAT BELT.

12:10.875 --> 12:12.583
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

12:12.667 --> 12:14.125
WE HAVE TO GO NOW.

12:14.208 --> 12:16.125
HOLD ON.

12:16.208 --> 12:18.417
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY,
LITTLE GOOSE. MOMMY'S HERE.

12:18.500 --> 12:19.792
WHAT ABOUT DAD?
IS DAD COMING?

12:19.875 --> 12:22.625
DAD?!

12:22.709 --> 12:25.375
[ CRASHING ]

12:25.458 --> 12:27.291
Jordi:
CAN I OPEN MY EYES NOW?

12:27.375 --> 12:28.375
NOT YET.

12:28.458 --> 12:29.917
YOU'RE FREAKING ME OUT.

12:30.000 --> 12:32.000
OKAY.

12:34.709 --> 12:36.750
UM...
IS OUTSIDE THE SURPRISE?

12:36.834 --> 12:38.250
I MEAN,
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

12:38.333 --> 12:40.625
I JUST WANT TO GAUGE
MY LEVEL OF EXCITEMENT HERE.

12:40.709 --> 12:42.959
WAIT FOR IT.
♪ WELL, YOU DON'T KNOW ♪

12:43.041 --> 12:45.834
[ HORN HONKS ]
♪ WHAT WE CAN FIND ♪

12:45.917 --> 12:47.333
[ TIRES SCREECH ]
♪ WHY DON'T YOU COME WITH ME,
LITTLE GIRL ♪

12:47.417 --> 12:49.458
SO...
♪ ON A MAGIC CARPET RIDE ♪

12:49.542 --> 12:50.959
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

12:51.041 --> 12:52.750
NICE CAR, MAN.
♪ WELL, YOU DON'T KNOW ♪

12:52.834 --> 12:54.709
[ CHUCKLES ]
"NICE"?
♪ WHAT WE CAN SEE ♪

12:54.792 --> 12:56.750
"NICE"?
♪ WHY DON'T YOU TELL
YOUR DREAMS TO ME ♪

12:56.834 --> 12:58.959
[ CAR TURNS OFF ]

12:59.041 --> 13:01.625
THERE ARE FIVE OF THESE
IN THE WORLD.

13:01.709 --> 13:03.458
THIS COLOR IS DISCONTINUED.

13:03.542 --> 13:05.458
THE SEATS ARE ITALIAN LEATHER.

13:05.542 --> 13:08.959
AND DAVID BOWIE ONCE LEANED
RIGHT HERE.

13:09.041 --> 13:11.125
IT'S A REALLY NICE CAR?

13:11.208 --> 13:12.834
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:12.917 --> 13:16.208
SO, WORD ON THE STREET IS
THAT TODAY YOU BECAME A MAN.

13:16.291 --> 13:19.333
NOW, THERE ARE
A LOT OF UNFORTUNATE THINGS

13:19.417 --> 13:21.834
THAT COME
WITH BEING AN ADULT --

13:21.917 --> 13:25.458
UNWANTED HAIR LOSS,
UNWANTED HAIR <i>GROWTH.</i>

13:25.542 --> 13:30.709
BUT DRIVING
IS ONE OF LIFE'S GREATEST PERKS.

13:30.792 --> 13:33.000
SO TAKE IT FOR A SPIN.
COME ON.

13:33.083 --> 13:34.792
FEEL THE WIND IN YOUR FACE.

13:34.875 --> 13:36.667
I-I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO DRIVE.

13:36.750 --> 13:37.834
I CAN TEACH YOU...

13:37.917 --> 13:39.625
IF YOU WANT.
REALLY?

13:39.709 --> 13:41.166
TH-THAT'D BE GREAT.

13:41.250 --> 13:43.041
I'LL GO GRAB MY LICENSE.

13:43.125 --> 13:46.333
UH, LISTEN, AS MUCH AS I
APPRECIATE A PROPER REBELLION,

13:46.417 --> 13:48.834
I-I DON'T THINK
I CAN ALLOW THIS, JORDI.

13:48.917 --> 13:50.834
YOU KNOW, MINORS TEACHING MINORS
TO DRIVE --

13:50.917 --> 13:55.291
IT'S, YOU KNOW,
FROWNED UPON/ILLEGAL.

13:59.625 --> 14:01.542
I HAVE CANCER...

14:01.625 --> 14:03.792
LIKE, EVERYWHERE.

14:05.959 --> 14:08.166
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]
GOD.

14:08.250 --> 14:11.542
CHEAP.
ALL RIGHT, FIVE-MILE RADIUS.

14:11.625 --> 14:13.542
SEAT BELTS.
AND NO TEXTING.

14:13.625 --> 14:15.417
OKAY.
HAVE FUN.

14:15.500 --> 14:17.208
HEY, AREN'T YOU
COMING WITH US?

14:17.291 --> 14:19.750
I THINK EMMA WOULD RATHER BE
ALONE, YOU KNOW, WITH YOU.

14:19.834 --> 14:21.500
LOOK, LEO,
I GET THAT YOU GUYS ARE A THING.

14:21.583 --> 14:23.041
HEY, WE USED TO BE A THING,
YOU KNOW?

14:23.125 --> 14:24.542
IT'S COOL.
WHATEVER YOU WANT TO DO.

14:24.625 --> 14:26.709
I PRETTY MUCH
WANT TO JUST KEEP IT EASY.

14:26.792 --> 14:28.709
ALL RIGHT? WE'RE JUST ALL
FRIENDS HERE, YOU KNOW?

14:28.792 --> 14:30.709
READY TO ROLL?
YOU COMING?

14:30.792 --> 14:33.542
YEAH, LET'S DO THIS.

14:33.625 --> 14:35.500
THIS IS GONNA BE FUN.

14:35.583 --> 14:37.750
IF YOU SAY SO.

14:37.834 --> 14:39.375
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

14:39.458 --> 14:41.583
<i>TOTALLY.</i>
<i>A TRIFECTA OF UNREQUITED LOVE</i>

14:41.667 --> 14:44.417
<i>CRAMMING INTO A CAR</i>
<i>AND HITTING THE OPEN ROAD --</i>

14:44.500 --> 14:45.917
<i>WHAT'S NOT FUN ABOUT THAT?</i>

14:46.000 --> 14:47.750
WHOA.
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

14:53.041 --> 14:54.625
OKAY. BAD NEWS.

14:54.709 --> 14:57.417
I KEVIN BACON-ED MY ASS
ALL AROUND THAT BUILDING,

14:57.500 --> 14:59.750
AND I CAME UP
WITH SIX DEGREES OF SQUAT.

14:59.834 --> 15:01.917
I DON'T KNOW
ANYONE WHO KNOWS ANYONE

15:02.000 --> 15:03.750
THAT LIVES
IN 10504 WILSHIRE.

15:03.834 --> 15:05.500
HOWEVER,
I DID SOME DIGGING,

15:05.583 --> 15:08.792
AND I FOUND OUT
THAT APARTMENT 5C IS EMPTY.

15:08.875 --> 15:10.250
BOOM.

15:10.333 --> 15:12.458
I ALREADY KNEW
THAT APARTMENT 5C WAS EMPTY.

15:12.542 --> 15:13.667
AIM HIGHER.

15:13.750 --> 15:16.000
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

15:16.083 --> 15:17.750
YOU'RE WASTING MY TIME.

15:17.834 --> 15:20.166
IT'S NOT LIKE I CAN GET INTO
AN EMPTY APARTMENT.

15:20.250 --> 15:23.166
WELL, <i>I</i> CAN.
HOW?

15:23.250 --> 15:25.000
MY MOMS
ARE PROPERTY WHORES.

15:25.083 --> 15:27.500
THEY HAVE A SUPERSTAR REALTOR
ON RETAINER.

15:27.583 --> 15:30.291
I COULD GET US IN THAT BUILDING
WITHIN AN HOUR.

15:30.375 --> 15:32.000
[ SIGHS ]

15:32.083 --> 15:33.375
ALL RIGHT. LET'S DO THIS.

15:33.458 --> 15:35.000
MNH-MNH.
FIRST, LET'S DO <i>THIS.</i>

15:35.083 --> 15:36.542
GIVE ME
SOMETHING TO GO ON

15:36.625 --> 15:38.959
SO I KNOW YOU'RE NOT
COMPLETELY FULL OF CRAP.

15:39.041 --> 15:40.667
ALL RIGHT. YOU KNOW
THIS BOARD OF PEOPLE

15:40.750 --> 15:42.542
YOU KEEP HEARING ABOUT --
THE ONES THAT DECIDE YOUR FATE?

15:42.625 --> 15:45.333
WELL, THEY'RE NOT SOME MAGICAL
GROUP OF WOODLAND FAIRIES,

15:45.417 --> 15:47.041
ALL RIGHT?
THEY ACTUALLY EXIST.

15:47.125 --> 15:52.333
AND THEY'RE ALL AROUND YOU,
WATCHING YOUR EVERY MOVE.

15:52.417 --> 15:54.458
OKAY. CREEPY. NOTED.

15:54.542 --> 15:56.208
PEOPLE WHO GET
ON THE U.N.O.S. LIST

15:56.291 --> 15:58.208
ARE NOT JUST PEOPLE
WHO NEED THE ORGAN.

15:58.291 --> 16:01.083
IT'S PEOPLE WHO THE BOARD FEELS
WILL TAKE CARE OF THE ORGAN.

16:01.166 --> 16:02.834
DO YOU KNOW
WHO'S ON THIS BOARD?

16:02.917 --> 16:04.583
I DO, INDEED, YEAH.

16:04.667 --> 16:06.041
OKAY. WHO?

16:06.125 --> 16:08.625
APARTMENT 5C.

16:14.500 --> 16:17.208
AFTER THOROUGHLY REVIEWING
YOUR SON'S MEDICAL HISTORY,

16:17.291 --> 16:19.291
WE'RE PREPARED
TO MAKE A RECOMMENDATION

16:19.375 --> 16:20.875
FOR HIS CARE
GOING FORWARD.

16:20.959 --> 16:22.667
<i>THIS SHOULD BE RIVETING.</i>

16:22.750 --> 16:25.041
CHARLIE HAS BEEN OUT OF THE ICU
NOW FOR OVER EIGHT WEEKS,

16:25.125 --> 16:27.709
AND THERE HAS BEEN NO CLINICAL
IMPROVEMENT IN HIS STATUS.

16:27.792 --> 16:29.166
THERE IS NO
FORESEEABLE EVIDENCE

16:29.250 --> 16:30.667
THAT HE WILL
COME OUT OF HIS COMA

16:30.750 --> 16:32.166
IN THE NEAR FUTURE,
IF EVER.

16:32.250 --> 16:34.000
IT IS OUR RECOMMENDATION
THAT CHARLIE BE REMOVED

16:34.083 --> 16:35.375
FROM THE ACUTE-HOSPITAL
SETTING

16:35.458 --> 16:36.709
TO ONE OF THE APPROVED
FACILITIES.

16:36.792 --> 16:38.667
YOU DON'T MEAN THIS IS IT,
DO YOU?

16:38.750 --> 16:40.000
WAIT A MINUTE, NOW.
WE HAVE TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT

16:40.083 --> 16:41.625
THAT THE E.E.G.
IS NOT FLAT

16:41.709 --> 16:43.917
AND THAT THERE IS DOMINANT
THETA-DELTA ACTIVITY,

16:44.000 --> 16:46.041
AND AS SUCH,
THE PROGNOSIS IS UNKNOWN.

16:46.125 --> 16:48.250
BUT FOR OUR PURPOSES,
WE HAVE NOT SEEN THE
CLINICAL IMPROVEMENT

16:48.333 --> 16:50.375
THAT WOULD JUSTIFY
CONTINUED INPATIENT CARE.

16:50.458 --> 16:52.125
<i>I CAN'T JUSTIFY YOUR JACKET,</i>
<i>EITHER,</i>

16:52.208 --> 16:54.041
<i>BUT AT LEAST</i>
<i>I'VE GOT SOME TACT, MAN.</i>

16:54.125 --> 16:56.083
WHAT ABOUT
FOR <i>CHARLIE'S</i> PURPOSES?

16:56.166 --> 16:58.458
WHAT ABOUT THE INTERVENTIONS
WE HAVEN'T EVEN TRIED YET?

16:58.542 --> 17:00.458
YOU WOULD NEED COUNTY APPROVAL
AT THIS POINT

17:00.542 --> 17:03.083
IF YOU WANTED TO GO FORWARD
WITH ANY EXPERIMENTAL THERAPIES.

17:03.166 --> 17:04.917
BUT, AGAIN, UH,
OUR RECOMMENDATION IS THAT

17:05.000 --> 17:06.959
THAT WOULD NOT BE
AN EFFICIENT USE OF FUNDING.

17:07.041 --> 17:08.875
WELL, I'M NOT SURE
"FUNDING" IS --

17:08.959 --> 17:10.750
DR. McANDREW,
TO THE BEST OF YOUR KNOWLEDGE,

17:10.834 --> 17:12.542
HAVE YOU DONE
EVERYTHING YOU CAN,

17:12.625 --> 17:14.875
REALISTICALLY, WITHIN YOUR
MEANS, TO HELP THIS PATIENT?

17:17.291 --> 17:18.667
REALISTICALLY, YES.

17:21.875 --> 17:24.792
WE ARE AWARE THAT
THIS IS A DIFFICULT DECISION,

17:24.875 --> 17:27.792
BUT IF YOU'RE
GOING TO APPEAL,

17:27.875 --> 17:30.375
YOU MUST EXERCISE THE OPTION
WITHIN 48 HOURS.

17:36.875 --> 17:39.375
[ MONITOR BEEPS STEADILY ]

17:41.750 --> 17:43.208
SO, YOU'RE GONNA
WANT TO MAKE SURE

17:43.291 --> 17:45.166
THAT YOUR HANDS ARE ON
9:00 AND 3:00 AT ALL TIMES.

17:45.250 --> 17:47.083
NOT ALL TIMES.
WHAT IF THIS WAS A STICK SHIFT?

17:47.166 --> 17:48.583
BUT IT'S NOT
A STICK SHIFT.

17:48.667 --> 17:49.959
WELL, HE'S GONNA DRIVE
MORE THAN ONE CAR.

17:50.041 --> 17:51.625
YOU'RE DOING GREAT,
JORDI.

17:51.709 --> 17:54.083
THANKS.

17:54.166 --> 17:55.792
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHERE WE ARE, BUT...

17:55.875 --> 17:57.250
OH, THIS IS HANCOCK PARK.

17:57.333 --> 17:59.000
IT'S ONE OF MY FAVORITE
NEIGHBORHOODS IN L.A.

17:59.083 --> 18:00.834
YOU KNOW, THE GIANT OAK TREES --
THE WHOLE THING

18:00.917 --> 18:02.583
KIND OF REMINDS ME
OF "GONE WITH THE WIND."

18:02.667 --> 18:05.041
YOU KNOW, WITH
THE CRUMBLING SOUTHERN MANSION.

18:05.125 --> 18:07.500
I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S LIKE THE STREET HAS A SOUL.

18:07.583 --> 18:09.834
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU SHOULD MEET MY <i>ABUELA.</i>

18:09.917 --> 18:12.000
SHE THINKS
EVERYTHING HAS A SOUL --

18:12.083 --> 18:14.834
ONIONS, RUGS,
STATION WAGONS.

18:14.917 --> 18:17.500
[ CHUCKLES ]
DOES SHE TALK TO THEM?
TALK TO THEM?

18:17.583 --> 18:19.500
SHE'S GOT A BLESSING
FOR EVERYTHING.

18:19.583 --> 18:22.000
IT SOUNDS LIKE SHIRLEY
IN THE PSYCH WARD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:22.083 --> 18:24.375
YOU KNOW, MY FAMILY WENT THROUGH
A SPIRITUAL PHASE ONCE.

18:24.458 --> 18:26.625
THEY THOUGHT THAT IF WE ALL
SAID GRACE TOGETHER,

18:26.709 --> 18:28.208
WE WOULD BE
MORE CONNECTED,

18:28.291 --> 18:30.625
BUT, UH, THE WHOLE THING
WAS PRETTY SAD SACK.

18:30.709 --> 18:32.250
AT LEAST YOU TRIED,
RIGHT?

18:34.417 --> 18:36.125
HEY, THANKS
FOR BEING SO PATIENT, EMMA.

18:36.208 --> 18:37.500
YOU'RE
A REALLY GOOD TEACHER.

18:37.583 --> 18:39.000
ANYTIME.

18:39.083 --> 18:41.041
<i>WHAT'S WORSE</i>
<i>THAN HAVING ONE LEG?</i>

18:41.125 --> 18:44.083
<i>FEELING LIKE A THIRD WHEEL.</i>

18:45.542 --> 18:47.333
<i>DING! DING! ROUND ONE</i>

18:47.417 --> 18:49.542
<i>OF THE CHARLIE HUTCHISON</i>
<i>HEAVYWEIGHT TITLE MATCH.</i>

18:49.625 --> 18:51.750
<i>IN THE MAROON SCRUBS,</i>
<i>WE HAVE NURSE JACKSON,</i>

18:51.834 --> 18:56.375
<i>AND IN LAST SEASON'S</i>
<i>CHUNKY TIE, DR. McANDREW.</i>

18:56.458 --> 18:58.875
[ SIGHS ] CASE MANAGERS
AREN'T GONNA BE SWAYED

18:58.959 --> 19:01.667
BY A HAIL-MARY PASS, DENA.
THEY LOOK AT STATISTICS,

19:01.750 --> 19:04.583
AND I COULD NOT LIE
ABOUT WHAT IS RIGHT IN
FRONT OF THEIR FACES.

19:04.667 --> 19:06.500
SO YOU DON'T THINK
HE'S GONNA WAKE UP?

19:06.583 --> 19:08.500
I DON'T KNOW.

19:08.583 --> 19:10.125
AND WHEN I'M CONFRONTED

19:10.208 --> 19:12.083
BY A LEGAL TEAM ASKING ME
BLACK-AND-WHITE QUESTIONS --

19:12.166 --> 19:13.667
THOSE PEOPLE
ARE LOOKING AT CHARLIE

19:13.750 --> 19:15.041
LIKE HE'S A POTENTIAL
EMPTY HOSPITAL BED,

19:15.125 --> 19:16.500
LIKE HE'S JUST
TAKING UP SPACE

19:16.583 --> 19:17.875
FROM SOMEONE ELSE
THEY COULD BE CHARGING.

19:17.959 --> 19:19.583
NOT SOMEONE ELSE.
ANOTHER SICK KID --

19:19.667 --> 19:21.667
A SICK KID WE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO ACTUALLY HELP.

19:21.750 --> 19:23.792
SO THAT'S IT.
WE GIVE UP.

19:23.875 --> 19:26.542
YOU JUST TELL THE PARENTS
TO GIVE UP?
DON'T TALK TO ME LIKE THAT.

19:26.625 --> 19:28.417
YOU DON'T THINK
THAT THIS KILLS ME, TOO?

19:28.500 --> 19:30.000
ACTUALLY, I DON'T.

19:30.083 --> 19:32.125
I DON'T THINK YOU CARE
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER.

19:33.959 --> 19:35.375
I'M WITH HIM EVERY DAY.

19:35.458 --> 19:36.834
FOR TWO MINUTES.

19:36.917 --> 19:38.917
NOW, I MADE A PROMISE
TO THAT LITTLE BOY,

19:39.000 --> 19:40.458
A PROMISE
I INTEND TO KEEP.

19:40.542 --> 19:42.542
YOU SHOULD KNOW
BETTER THAN ANYONE

19:42.625 --> 19:45.583
THAT WE DON'T MAKE PROMISES
HERE.

19:45.667 --> 19:49.291
[ TOM ODELL'S "HEAL" PLAYS ]

19:49.375 --> 19:51.709
Jackson: WE'RE JUST GONNA
HANG OUT HERE FOR A MINUTE

19:51.792 --> 19:54.250
BEFORE THEY'RE READY FOR YOU
IN THE O.R.

19:54.333 --> 19:57.583
WILL YOU TAKE A PICTURE
OF MY GUTS WHEN I'M OPENED UP?

19:57.667 --> 19:59.000
I WILL NOT.

19:59.083 --> 20:01.083
I'M NOT TAKING SELFIES
WITH YOUR INSIDES

20:01.166 --> 20:02.583
WHEN I'VE GOT A JOB TO DO.

20:02.667 --> 20:04.458
♪ TAKE MY MIND
AND TAKE MY PAIN ♪

20:04.542 --> 20:06.709
WE COULD MAYBE
GET SOMEONE ELSE TO DO IT.

20:06.792 --> 20:10.917
♪ LIKE AN EMPTY BOTTLE
TAKES THE RAIN ♪

20:11.000 --> 20:12.709
COOL.

20:14.542 --> 20:16.291
I'M SCARED.

20:16.375 --> 20:17.792
♪ AND HEAL ♪

20:17.875 --> 20:20.625
I GET THAT WAY SOMETIMES.

20:20.709 --> 20:23.750
NOT A GOOD FEELING.

20:23.834 --> 20:26.667
YOU WANT TO KNOW ABOUT ONE OF
THE TIMES I WAS MOST SCARED?

20:26.750 --> 20:29.959
♪ TAKE MY PAST
AND TAKE MY SINS ♪

20:30.041 --> 20:32.125
I WAS ABOUT YOUR AGE.

20:32.208 --> 20:36.333
I WAS WALKING HOME
FROM A FRIEND'S HOUSE BY MYSELF,

20:36.417 --> 20:39.166
AND THIS STORM HIT.

20:39.250 --> 20:43.083
[ SIGHS ]
THE SKY WAS DUMPING RAIN...

20:43.166 --> 20:47.667
LIGHTNING SPLIT A TREE IN HALF
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.

20:47.750 --> 20:50.917
I WAS SO SCARED.
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:51.000 --> 20:57.166
OH, I JUST SAT DOWN BY A ROCK
AND STARTED CRYING.

20:57.250 --> 21:01.000
BUT AFTER A MINUTE
OF SITTING THERE IN THE DARK,

21:01.083 --> 21:04.000
I TOOK A BREATH
AND A LITTLE STEP...

21:04.083 --> 21:06.166
AND THEN ANOTHER ONE,

21:06.250 --> 21:09.291
'CAUSE I KNEW
THAT WAS ALL I COULD DO.

21:09.375 --> 21:13.500
SO, NEXT BREATH,
NEXT STEP...

21:13.583 --> 21:15.125
TILL I WAS HOME AGAIN.

21:17.083 --> 21:20.166
BECAUSE THERE'S ALWAYS
A WAY HOME.

21:20.250 --> 21:22.500
YOU'RE GONNA FIND YOUR WAY
OUT OF THIS, CHARLIE.

21:22.583 --> 21:25.000
AND WHEN YOU WAKE UP...

21:25.083 --> 21:28.625
I WILL BE RIGHT HERE.

21:28.709 --> 21:30.041
I PROMISE YOU THAT.

21:32.291 --> 21:34.250
I'LL BE RIGHT HERE.

21:35.500 --> 21:38.375
MAKE SURE
YOU STAY TO THE LEFT, JORDI.

21:38.458 --> 21:40.333
YOU DON'T WANT TO ACCIDENTLY
GET ON THE FREEWAY.
THE FREEWAY?

21:40.417 --> 21:41.834
HEY, GUYS, WATCH OUT.
POLICE REPORTED AHEAD.

21:41.917 --> 21:43.667
DON'T LISTEN TO HIM.

21:43.750 --> 21:46.709
I'M NOT SAYING WATCH OUT --
THE APP IS SAYING WATCH OUT,

21:46.792 --> 21:48.333
AND THE APP
IS AN UNBIASED THIRD PARTY.

21:48.417 --> 21:50.875
HEY, DUDE, STOP SIGN!
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

21:50.959 --> 21:52.709
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SCREAM,
ALL RIGHT?

21:52.792 --> 21:54.291
I'M SURE
THAT HE SAW THE SIGN.

21:54.375 --> 21:56.208
ACTUALLY, I-I DIDN'T
SEE THE STOP SIGN.

21:56.291 --> 21:58.500
THE SCREAMING WAS HELPFUL.
[ HORN HONKS ]

21:58.583 --> 22:00.083
A RULE OF THUMB
MY DAD TAUGHT ME

22:00.166 --> 22:01.917
WAS TO ALWAYS STAY
THREE CAR LENGTHS BEHIND.

22:02.000 --> 22:04.041
YOU KNOW, YOU RIDE UP TOO CLOSE,
AND YOU'LL GET INTO AN ACCIDENT.

22:04.125 --> 22:06.333
IT'S AMAZING HOW YOU CAN MAKE
YOURSELF THE CENTER OF ATTENTION

22:06.417 --> 22:08.333
EVEN WHEN YOU'RE LITERALLY
SITTING IN THE BACK SEAT.

22:08.417 --> 22:10.500
WELL, I THOUGHT THIS WAS
SUPPOSED TO BE A DRIVING LESSON.

22:10.583 --> 22:13.041
AND I THOUGHT
THIS WAS SUPPOSED TO BE FUN.
HEY, WELL, I'M HAVING FUN.

22:13.125 --> 22:15.083
LOOK, I DON'T MEAN TO RIDE YOU,
MAN. I JUST THOUGHT

22:15.166 --> 22:17.417
I COULD GIVE YOU A FEW POINTERS,
YOU KNOW, SINCE, APPARENTLY,

22:17.500 --> 22:19.667
I'M THE ONLY ONE IN HERE
WHO ACTUALLY KNOWS HOW TO DRIVE.

22:19.750 --> 22:22.500
WELL, IT'S NOT LIKE YOU CAN
DRIVE WELL ANYMORE, RIGHT?

22:23.959 --> 22:25.709
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

22:25.792 --> 22:27.250
I'M GETTING
KIND OF TIRED, GUYS.

22:27.333 --> 22:28.834
IS IT OKAY
IF WE HEAD BACK NOW?

22:28.917 --> 22:30.542
OF COURSE.
YEAH, WHATEVER YOU WANT.

22:30.625 --> 22:31.792
GREAT.

22:39.083 --> 22:40.834
CAN I HELP YOU?
YEAH. KARA SOUDERS.

22:40.917 --> 22:42.875
I'M HERE TO SEE MY REALTOR,
HOLLY OLLIS.

22:42.959 --> 22:44.291
HAVE A SEAT.

22:46.458 --> 22:48.208
BAM. IN YOUR FACE.

22:48.291 --> 22:50.583
NOW, ARE YOU GONNA TELL ME
WHAT WE'RE DOING HERE?

22:50.667 --> 22:52.667
CHILL, GRASSHOPPER.

22:56.291 --> 22:58.166
[ SIGHS ]

23:02.000 --> 23:03.375
OH, MY GOD.

23:03.458 --> 23:05.083
IS THIS YOUR FIRST TIME
OUT OF THE GHETTO?

23:05.166 --> 23:06.542
[ GASPS ]
SHOULD WE TAKE A SELFIE?

23:06.625 --> 23:08.375
BITCH,
I'M FROM BRENTWOOD.

23:08.458 --> 23:10.583
MY FATHER TEACHES POLI SCI
AT UCLA.

23:10.667 --> 23:13.083
YEAH, LIKE I INVENTED
RACIAL PROFILING.

23:13.166 --> 23:16.625
WHATEVER. YOU SEEM FREAKISHLY
IMPRESSED BY WALNUT PANELING.

23:16.709 --> 23:18.250
HELLO! HELLO!

23:18.333 --> 23:19.917
HEY.
SORRY I'M LATE.

23:20.000 --> 23:21.583
MWAH! MWAH!          MWAH! MWAH!

23:21.667 --> 23:23.417
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR MEETING US.
OF COURSE.

23:23.500 --> 23:25.458
OKAY, SO THIS IS
KIND OF ON THE D.L.,

23:25.542 --> 23:27.250
BUT ONE OF MY MOMS
MIGHT BE LOOKING

23:27.333 --> 23:29.583
FOR A LITTLE ESCAPE HATCH.
I'M DOING A SMIDGLE OF RECON.

23:29.667 --> 23:30.959
OHH, SAY NO MORE.

23:31.041 --> 23:33.208
AND YOU ARE?
[ GASPS ] OH.

23:33.291 --> 23:35.291
THIS IS DASHIELL,
MY DESIGNER.

23:35.375 --> 23:36.417
HE'S A GENIUS.

23:36.500 --> 23:38.500
FABULOUS.
SHALL WE?

23:38.583 --> 23:42.542
DON'T FORGET THE BAG, DASH.

23:52.417 --> 23:54.792
<i>THAT'S A TERRA-RAPTOR --</i>
<i>SMALL AND VICIOUS,</i>

23:54.875 --> 23:57.417
<i>IT WILL STOP AT NOTHING</i>
<i>TO KILL HIS OPPONENT.</i>

23:57.500 --> 23:59.041
<i>ISN'T HE SO CUTE?</i>

24:00.208 --> 24:02.000
WHERE DID THIS COME FROM?
<i>BUSTED.</i>

24:02.083 --> 24:04.250
I DON'T THINK
I'VE EVER SEEN THAT BEFORE.

24:04.333 --> 24:07.500
LISTEN, MANDY, I WANT
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT
WHAT WAS SAID EARLIER.

24:07.583 --> 24:10.291
HOW LONG
HAS HE BEEN COMING HERE?
<i>MOM, PLEASE DON'T START.</i>

24:10.375 --> 24:12.959
I DON'T THINK THIS
IS WHERE YOU WANT TO
BE FOCUSING YOUR --

24:13.041 --> 24:14.667
HOW LONG?
HE'S THE BOY'S FATHER.

24:14.750 --> 24:16.959
WHOSE SIDE ARE YOU ON?
I'M ON CHARLIE'S SIDE.

24:17.041 --> 24:18.458
<i>I'M</i> ON CHARLIE'S SIDE.

24:18.542 --> 24:20.458
THAT'S WHY I WAS KEEPING NICK
AWAY FROM HIM.

24:20.542 --> 24:24.375
THAT WAS A DECISION THAT I MADE
WHICH YOU AGREED TO HONOR.

24:27.875 --> 24:29.709
MAND--
[ SIGHS ]

24:34.250 --> 24:35.375
[ SIGHS ]

24:35.458 --> 24:38.166
OH, SWEETIE...

24:38.250 --> 24:40.750
JUST THIS ONCE,
I HOPE YOU DIDN'T HEAR THAT.

24:42.000 --> 24:45.083
<i>YEAH, I WISH I DIDN'T, EITHER.</i>

24:52.417 --> 24:54.875
HI. I'M BRITTANY DOBLER,
HERE TO MEET NURSE JACKSON.

24:54.959 --> 24:57.208
JUST A SECOND.
DO I HAVE ANYTHING IN MY TEETH?

24:57.291 --> 24:59.166
I JUST HAD
A SESAME BAGEL.

24:59.250 --> 25:01.500
SO DUMB, RIGHT? I MEAN,
I ALWAYS EAT WHEN I'M NERVOUS,

25:01.583 --> 25:03.208
AND JOB INTERVIEWS
MAKE ME NERVOUS,

25:03.291 --> 25:05.500
ESPECIALLY 'CAUSE I HEAR
THIS WOMAN IS KIND OF MEAN.

25:05.583 --> 25:07.458
SO, CAN YOU POINT HER OUT?
IS SHE AROUND?

25:12.000 --> 25:14.709
OH.

25:14.792 --> 25:16.750
HI.
I'M BRITTANY DOBLER...

25:16.834 --> 25:20.125
THE WOMAN WHO IS PROBABLY
NOT GONNA GET THIS JOB.

25:22.291 --> 25:23.875
DON'T MOVE.

25:23.959 --> 25:26.041
HEY. SHOULDN'T YOU BE
IN SURGERY WITH LEO ROTH?

25:26.125 --> 25:28.375
YEAH. I'M GOING IN NOW.
MOM HAD A LITTLE, UH --

25:28.458 --> 25:30.208
A LITTLE CASE
OF COLD FEET,

25:30.291 --> 25:32.291
BUT WE'RE BACK ON TRACK.
ANYTHING ELSE GOING ON?

25:32.375 --> 25:35.375
JUST THEM.
Mandy: I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU WERE THINKING.

25:35.458 --> 25:37.875
I <i>WASN'T</i> THINKING.
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

25:37.959 --> 25:40.208
I CAN'T EVEN LOOK AT YOU
RIGHT NOW.

25:40.291 --> 25:41.834
THEIR KID IN SURGERY YET?

25:41.917 --> 25:43.834
ABOUT AN HOUR NOW.

25:43.917 --> 25:45.750
[ SIGHS ]

25:45.834 --> 25:47.417
HEY.

25:47.500 --> 25:49.458
CAN I GET YOU GUYS ANYTHING?
A CUP OF COFFEE, MAYBE?

25:49.542 --> 25:51.792
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH LONGER
THE SURGERY'S GOING TO TAKE?

25:51.875 --> 25:53.417
WILL SOMEBODY BE DOWN
TO LET US KNOW?

25:53.500 --> 25:54.917
I'LL CHECK IN
WITH DR. POTTER --

25:55.000 --> 25:57.250
SEE IF WE CAN'T
GET AN UPDATE.

25:57.333 --> 26:01.083
MEANTIME, I'M GONNA NEED
YOU BOTH TO BE A UNITED FRONT.

26:01.166 --> 26:03.750
YOU'RE CHARLIE'S PARENTS.
YOU'RE ALL HE'S GOT.

26:03.834 --> 26:07.041
SO, ONE OF YOU TAKE A WALK,
ONE OF YOU HAVE SOME COFFEE --

26:07.125 --> 26:09.583
WHATEVER YOU NEED TO DO
TO GET THROUGH THIS,

26:09.667 --> 26:12.333
BECAUSE RIGHT NOW,
WE'RE ALL ON TEAM CHARLIE.

26:13.667 --> 26:15.500
I NEED SOME AIR.

26:22.125 --> 26:23.709
<i>PLEASE DON'T CRY,</i>
<i>NURSE JACKSON.</i>

26:23.792 --> 26:26.458
<i>IF YOU CRY,</i>
<i>THEN</i> I'M <i>GONNA CRY.</i>

26:26.542 --> 26:28.792
[ <i>SIGHS</i> ]
<i>IF YOU DON'T MIND,</i>

26:28.875 --> 26:31.542
<i>I THINK I NEED TO BE ALONE</i>
<i>FOR A MINUTE.</i>

26:36.625 --> 26:40.375
WELL, HERE WE ARE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:40.458 --> 26:41.458
OHH.

26:45.333 --> 26:47.583
SO...
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

26:47.667 --> 26:49.917
YEAH. WHAT DO YOU THINK,
DASHIELL?

26:50.000 --> 26:51.417
THE LINES --

26:51.500 --> 26:53.709
THEY'RE A BIT EXPECTED,

26:53.792 --> 26:55.875
BUT I-I THINK
WE CAN SHAKE THINGS UP

26:55.959 --> 26:57.583
WITH A LITTLE BIT OF TEXTURE.

26:57.667 --> 27:00.917
LIKE, THIS WHOLE AREA IS BEGGING
FOR AN IMPUDENT WALLPAPER.

27:01.000 --> 27:03.375
I CAN SEE THAT.

27:03.458 --> 27:04.875
I'LL NEED TO BE
IN THE SPACE ALONE,

27:04.959 --> 27:06.709
JUST TO REALLY GET A SENSE
OF THE -- THE STORY.

27:06.792 --> 27:08.375
YEAH, TH-THIS IS HOW HE WORKS.

27:08.458 --> 27:11.250
[ CHUCKLES ] ABSOLUTELY.
I WILL LEAVE YOU GUYS.

27:11.333 --> 27:12.458
MWAH!

27:12.542 --> 27:14.625
WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

27:17.000 --> 27:18.917
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

27:19.000 --> 27:22.667
OKAY, SERIOUSLY,
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE?

27:25.834 --> 27:27.458
HELLO?

27:27.542 --> 27:29.083
♪ THIS IS A WORLD PREMIERE ♪

27:29.166 --> 27:30.709
♪ THIS IS A WORLD PREMIERE ♪

27:30.792 --> 27:32.291
♪ I DONE BEEN THROUGH
A WHOLE LOT ♪

27:32.375 --> 27:34.083
♪ TRIAL, TRIBULATION,
BUT I KNOW GOD ♪

27:34.166 --> 27:36.000
♪ SATAN WANNA PUT ME
IN A BOW TIE ♪

27:36.083 --> 27:38.917
♪ PRAYING THAT THE HOLY WATER
DON'T GO DRY ♪

27:39.000 --> 27:41.083
IF YOU'RE PLANNING ON JUMPING,
DON'T YOU THINK

27:41.166 --> 27:43.583
WE SHOULD AT LEAST DISCUSS
YOU GIVING ME YOUR HEART?

27:43.667 --> 27:45.291
♪ IN FRONT OF A DIRTY
DOUBLE-MIRROR THEY FOUND ME ♪

27:45.375 --> 27:46.792
♪ AND I LOVE MYSELF ♪

27:46.875 --> 27:48.417
OHH!

27:48.500 --> 27:50.834
NOW I GET IT.
YOU'RE A VANDAL.

27:50.917 --> 27:52.166
CAN YOU STEP BACK,
PLEASE?

27:52.250 --> 27:54.625
♪ I LOVE MYSELF ♪

27:54.709 --> 27:56.917
♪ HE SAID I GOTTA GET UP,
LIFE IS MORE THAN SUICIDE ♪

27:57.000 --> 27:58.291
♪ I LOVE MYSELF ♪

27:58.375 --> 27:59.625
ARE YOU, LIKE, AN ARTIST?

27:59.709 --> 28:01.291
NOT IF YOU KEEP TALKING.

28:01.375 --> 28:03.125
♪ EVERYBODY LOOKING AT YOU
CRAZY ♪

28:03.208 --> 28:04.792
♪ WHAT YOU GONE DO? ♪
♪ WHAT YOU GONE DO? ♪

28:04.875 --> 28:07.625
♪ LIFT UP YOUR HEAD
AND KEEP MOVING ♪

28:07.709 --> 28:09.583
♪ OR LET THE PARANOIA
HAUNT YOU ♪

28:09.667 --> 28:12.125
♪ EVERYBODY LACK CONFIDENCE,
EVERYBODY LACK CONFIDENCE ♪

28:12.208 --> 28:13.875
♪ HOW MANY TIMES OUR POTENTIAL
WAS ANONYMOUS? ♪

28:13.959 --> 28:15.667
♪ HOW MANY TIMES THE CITY
MAKING ME PROMISES? ♪

28:15.750 --> 28:16.959
♪ SO I PROMISE THIS ♪

28:17.041 --> 28:18.750
♪ I LOVE MYSELF ♪

28:18.834 --> 28:20.417
♪ THE WORLD IS A GHETTO
WITH GUNS AND PICKET SIGNS ♪

28:20.500 --> 28:22.583
♪ I LOVE MYSELF ♪

28:22.667 --> 28:24.792
♪ BUT IT CAN DO WHAT IT
WANT WHENEVER IT WANTS,
I DON'T MIND ♪

28:24.875 --> 28:26.667
♪ I LOVE MYSELF ♪

28:26.750 --> 28:28.125
♪ HE SAID I GOTTA GET UP,
LIFE IS MORE THAN SUICIDE ♪

28:28.208 --> 28:30.083
WHOA.
THAT'S SHOCKINGLY GOOD.

28:30.166 --> 28:31.834
I KNOW.

28:31.917 --> 28:36.000
BUT, I MEAN, WHY HERE?
NO ONE'S EVEN GONNA SEE IT.

28:36.083 --> 28:37.667
IS THIS, LIKE,
A BANKSY THING?

28:37.750 --> 28:39.333
YOU KNOW ABOUT BANKSY?

28:39.417 --> 28:42.625
WHATEVER. YOU KNOW ABOUT
IMPUDENT WALLPAPER.

28:42.709 --> 28:44.709
SURPRISES ALL AROUND.

28:51.250 --> 28:53.250
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

29:00.875 --> 29:02.792
WHAT HAPPENED?
WHAT'D THEY SAY?

29:02.875 --> 29:04.375
WE HAD A DEAL, NICK.

29:04.458 --> 29:06.959
WHAT DO YOU MEAN? ARE THE
INSURANCE GUYS STILL HERE?

29:07.041 --> 29:08.834
I FOUND YOUR LITTLE
"GAMIVERSE" GUY.

29:08.917 --> 29:10.500
I KNOW
YOU'VE BEEN WITH CHARLIE.

29:10.583 --> 29:12.667
DOES IT EVEN MATTER?
OF COURSE IT MATTERS.

29:12.750 --> 29:15.041
OH, WE BOTH KNOW
THAT RESTRAINING ORDER WAS CRAP.

29:15.125 --> 29:17.709
IF I'D HAVE GONE TO COURT
TO FIGHT IT, I WOULD HAVE WON,

29:17.792 --> 29:19.333
AND YOU KNOW IT.
BUT I DIDN'T,

29:19.417 --> 29:22.041
BECAUSE I'VE BEEN TOO BUSY
HATING MYSELF

29:22.125 --> 29:23.500
MORE THAN
YOU CAN EVER HATE ME.

29:23.583 --> 29:25.250
NOW, WHAT DID THEY SAY
ABOUT CHARLIE?

29:38.166 --> 29:41.375
I'M SORRY
IF MY BEING HERE UPSET YOU.

29:41.458 --> 29:43.375
BUT HONESTLY...

29:43.458 --> 29:46.083
WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES IT EVEN MAKE ANYMORE?

29:47.834 --> 29:49.792
IT'S NEVER GOING TO CHANGE.

29:52.291 --> 29:54.917
AS YOU KNOW, YOUR SON HAD
A SPLENIC LACERATION

29:55.000 --> 29:56.709
AND INTRA-ABDOMINAL
BLEEDING

29:56.792 --> 29:59.917
THAT WE WENT INTO
THE OPERATING ROOM TO CONTROL.

30:00.000 --> 30:02.291
BUT HE ALSO SUSTAINED
TRAUMA TO HIS HEAD

30:02.375 --> 30:05.458
AND HAS HAD SIGNIFICANT
INTRACRANIAL BLEEDING AND EDEMA.

30:05.542 --> 30:07.375
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT THAT MEANS.

30:07.458 --> 30:09.166
JUST TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENS NEXT.

30:09.250 --> 30:11.583
WELL, IT'S DIFFICULT TO MAKE
PREDICTIONS AT THIS POINT.

30:11.667 --> 30:13.917
MOST COMAS DON'T LAST
MORE THAN TWO TO FOUR WEEKS.

30:14.000 --> 30:15.208
WAIT -- COMA?

30:15.291 --> 30:17.625
I'M SORRY,
MR. AND MRS. HUTCHISON.

30:17.709 --> 30:20.542
YOUR SON HASN'T WOKEN UP
FROM SURGERY YET.

30:20.625 --> 30:23.208
I'M NOT SURE WHEN
OR <i>IF</i> HE EVER WILL.

30:37.875 --> 30:39.583
I THINK I LEFT MY PHONE
IN THE CAR.

30:39.667 --> 30:41.333
I'LL GET IT.
SEE YOU GUYS UPSTAIRS.

30:41.417 --> 30:44.917
THANKS.

30:45.000 --> 30:46.959
HEY, EMMA?

30:47.041 --> 30:47.959
EMMA!

30:48.041 --> 30:49.792
WHAT?

30:49.875 --> 30:51.250
I'M SORRY, OKAY?

30:51.333 --> 30:53.166
WHAT ARE YOU SORRY FOR NOW?
[ SIGHS ]

30:53.250 --> 30:55.417
CAN YOU JUST ACCEPT THE APOLOGY
AND STOP BEING SUCH A BITCH?

30:55.500 --> 30:57.000
[ Chuckling ] WOW.

30:57.083 --> 30:58.834
WORST APOLOGY EVER.

31:00.875 --> 31:02.792
I SHOULDN'T HAVE SAID
WHAT I SAID THE OTHER DAY

31:02.875 --> 31:04.667
ABOUT YOU BEING IN THE HOSPITAL
BY CHOICE.

31:04.750 --> 31:06.333
IT WAS A STUPID,
MISINFORMED THING TO SAY.

31:06.417 --> 31:07.959
I'M THE WORST PERSON EVER,
OKAY?

31:08.041 --> 31:10.792
YOU DON'T HAVE TO APOLOGIZE.
IT'S MY FAULT, REALLY.

31:10.875 --> 31:13.667
I-I SHOULD HAVE
SEEN IT COMING.
SEEN WHAT COMING?

31:13.750 --> 31:16.667
YOU MAKE THIS WHOLE OVERTURE
LIKE YOU ACTUALLY CARE.

31:16.750 --> 31:18.458
YOU KNOW,
LIKE YOU SEE ME.

31:18.542 --> 31:21.000
AND THE WHOLE TIME,
YOU'RE REALLY INTO KARA.

31:21.083 --> 31:23.834
THAT'S WHAT THIS IS ABOUT?
YOU THINK I LIKE KARA?

31:23.917 --> 31:26.500
I DON'T KNOW WHY I PRETENDED
YOU COULD BE ANYTHING

31:26.583 --> 31:28.834
OTHER THAN THE ALPHA MALE
AMERICAN DREAM --

31:28.917 --> 31:31.166
THE ATHLETE,
THE POPULAR GUY.

31:31.250 --> 31:32.875
THE ONE-LEGGED
CANCER PATIENT.

31:32.959 --> 31:34.667
PLEASE. YOU'RE GONNA COME
THROUGH THIS WHOLE THING

31:34.750 --> 31:36.375
BRIGHTER AND SHINIER...

31:36.458 --> 31:38.500
WITH A BRIGHT, SHINY CHEERLEADER
AS A TAKE-HOME PRIZE.

31:38.583 --> 31:40.166
SHE'S THE NATURAL FINISH
TO YOUR SENTENCE.

31:40.250 --> 31:42.333
CAN WE PAUSE
JUST FOR A SECOND

31:42.417 --> 31:45.291
TO ACKNOWLEDGE THAT I DISAGREE
WITH EVERYTHING YOU'RE SAYING?
WHY BOTHER?

31:45.375 --> 31:47.125
WHY BOTHER WITH ME?

31:47.208 --> 31:49.166
DON'T SLUM IT
ON MY ACCOUNT, LEO,

31:49.250 --> 31:51.166
BECAUSE I DON'T CARE
WHAT YOU DO.

31:51.250 --> 31:53.667
REALLY? 'CAUSE YOU'RE KIND OF
ACTING LIKE A PERSON WHO CARES.

31:53.750 --> 31:56.333
HOW IS IT OKAY FOR YOU TO BE
THIS SELF-RIGHTEOUSLY ANGRY?

31:56.417 --> 31:57.959
IT MAKES NO SENSE.

31:58.041 --> 32:00.875
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO INSISTED
WE SHOULD JUST BE FRIENDS.

32:00.959 --> 32:02.834
YEAH, WELL, I CHANGED MY MIND,
ALL RIGHT?

32:02.917 --> 32:05.125
I DON'T WANT TO BE FRIENDS!
GREAT! NEITHER DO I.

32:12.000 --> 32:15.000
<i>THAT, MY FRIENDS,</i>
<i>IS A DECLARATION OF LOVE...</i>

32:19.500 --> 32:21.750
<i>...AND WAR.</i>

32:31.709 --> 32:35.291
<i>OH, MAN. I DON'T KNOW</i>
<i>IF I CAN WATCH THIS.</i>

32:35.375 --> 32:37.291
<i>GOOD THING</i>
<i>MY EYES ARE CLOSED.</i>

32:37.375 --> 32:39.083
YOU'RE RIGHT.

32:42.125 --> 32:46.625
I SHOULD HAVE SAID SOMETHING
ABOUT NICK.

32:46.709 --> 32:48.792
AT THE TIME,
I DIDN'T WANT TO COMPLICATE

32:48.875 --> 32:51.166
AN ALREADY COMPLICATED
SITUATION.

32:51.250 --> 32:54.834
BUT GETTING IN THE MIDDLE
OF YOUR FAMILY'S BUSINESS --

32:54.917 --> 32:58.000
THAT'S JUST --
THERE'S NO EXCUSE, SO...

32:58.083 --> 33:00.208
I'M SORRY.

33:00.291 --> 33:04.000
IT'S OKAY.

33:04.083 --> 33:06.166
[ SIGHS ] IT'S NOT EVEN
ABOUT THAT ANYMORE.

33:06.250 --> 33:10.625
I THINK I WANTED IT TO BE ABOUT
SOMETHING AS SIMPLE AS THAT.

33:12.709 --> 33:14.834
NICK'S RIGHT.

33:14.917 --> 33:16.792
NOTHING'S EVER GONNA CHANGE.

33:16.875 --> 33:18.792
YOU GUYS HAVE DONE
ALL YOU CAN.

33:18.875 --> 33:22.583
IF HE HASN'T WOKEN UP BY NOW,
HE PROBABLY NEVER WILL.

33:22.667 --> 33:25.041
MANDY,
YOU CAN'T THINK LIKE THAT.

33:25.125 --> 33:27.333
NOW IS NOT THE TIME
TO GIVE UP.

33:27.417 --> 33:28.709
IT'S NOT GIVING UP.

33:28.792 --> 33:31.709
IT'S MORE LIKE...

33:31.792 --> 33:34.875
ACCEPTING THE TRUTH.

33:34.959 --> 33:39.208
ALL THIS TIME SINCE THAT NIGHT,
EVERYTHING I'VE DONE --

33:39.291 --> 33:42.542
SHUTTING OUT NICK,
KEEPING MY HEAD DOWN --

33:42.625 --> 33:46.375
I'VE JUST BEEN HOLDING ON
BY A THREAD FOR MYSELF.

33:46.458 --> 33:48.583
IT'S TIME FOR ME
TO THINK ABOUT

33:48.667 --> 33:51.000
WHAT'S ACTUALLY RIGHT
FOR CHARLIE.

33:54.125 --> 33:55.875
JUST GIVE IT
A MINUTE OR TWO,

33:55.959 --> 33:58.250
AND I WILL BE BACK
TO CHECK ON YOU, OKAY?

33:58.333 --> 33:59.500
[ AIR HISSING ]

33:59.583 --> 34:01.500
OH, DON'T EXCITE HIM.

34:01.583 --> 34:03.583
CAN I HELP IT?

34:03.667 --> 34:05.917
TIME TO PAY UP,
SNOT POCKET.

34:06.000 --> 34:07.542
GIVE ME A SECOND.

34:07.625 --> 34:09.750
I'M LOOSENING MY MUCUS
SO I DON'T DROWN TO DEATH.

34:09.834 --> 34:12.959
UGH. COME ON, DUDE.
OVERSHARE.

34:13.041 --> 34:16.291
[ SIGHS ]

34:16.375 --> 34:18.500
TODAY WAS MAYBE
TOO MUCH?

34:20.458 --> 34:22.709
SHOULD I BE FEELING BADLY
RIGHT NOW?

34:22.792 --> 34:25.166
'CAUSE I CAN MUSTER IT UP
IF NEED BE.

34:29.458 --> 34:31.291
WELL, IT <i>WAS</i> PRETTY FUN.

34:31.375 --> 34:34.583
GRANTED, MY BAR IS SUPER LOW
AT THIS POINT.

34:34.667 --> 34:37.083
BUT YOU'LL BE OKAY SOON,
RIGHT?

34:37.166 --> 34:39.083
I MEAN...

34:39.166 --> 34:41.041
YOUR TUNE-UP'S ALMOST OVER,

34:41.125 --> 34:44.375
AND THEN YOU'LL GET
YOUR NEW LUNGS AND...YAY!

34:44.458 --> 34:47.750
RIGHT?

34:47.834 --> 34:49.750
[ SWITCH CLICKS, HISSING STOPS ]
MAYBE...

34:49.834 --> 34:51.750
<i>IF</i> I DECIDE
TO HAVE THE SURGERY --

34:51.834 --> 34:52.959
BIG IF.

34:53.041 --> 34:54.583
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

34:54.667 --> 34:56.750
WHY WOULDN'T YOU
HAVE THE SURGERY?

34:56.834 --> 35:00.583
BECAUSE...

35:00.667 --> 35:03.083
NEW LUNGS WORK,
BUT FOR HOW LONG, YOU KNOW?

35:03.166 --> 35:06.500
IT'S NOT LIKE I'M GONNA SUDDENLY
LIVE A NORMAL LIFE.

35:06.583 --> 35:08.625
I GAVE THAT UP
A LONG TIME AGO.

35:08.709 --> 35:11.333
MY PARENTS ARE STILL
BENDING OVER BACKWARDS

35:11.417 --> 35:13.125
TO TRY TO SAVE ME,

35:13.208 --> 35:15.458
SO IF I <i>WAS</i> TO HAVE THE SURGERY,
IT'D BE FOR THEM.

35:15.542 --> 35:17.333
ME?

35:17.417 --> 35:19.917
I MADE MY PEACE.

35:20.000 --> 35:21.834
IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M GONNA LIVE FOREVER.

35:27.709 --> 35:29.750
I JUST WANT TO BE
REMEMBERED.

35:31.959 --> 35:34.709
THAT'S WHY YOU PAINTED
SOMETHING ON A ROOF

35:34.792 --> 35:36.250
NO ONE WILL EVER SEE.

35:41.625 --> 35:42.709
HEY, RUBEN.

35:42.792 --> 35:43.959
LEO! GLAD I CAUGHT YOU.

35:44.041 --> 35:45.709
I LEFT SOME LIBATIONS
IN YOUR ROOM.

35:45.792 --> 35:48.000
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?
YOU KNOW,
THEME OF THE DAY.

35:48.083 --> 35:50.875
YOU CAN'T TAKE IT WITH YOU -- AT
LEAST THROUGH AIRPORT SECURITY.

35:50.959 --> 35:52.542
OH, YOU'RE REALLY
LEAVING TONIGHT?

35:52.625 --> 35:54.875
YEAH, 11:00 FLIGHT.
A STOPOVER IN PARIS.

35:54.959 --> 35:56.667
THAT'S GREAT.
LET'S, UH, GRAB THE LIBATIONS,

35:56.750 --> 35:59.291
YOU KNOW,
FIND THE OTHERS --
I DON'T DO GOODBYES, KID.

36:01.750 --> 36:03.291
[ SIGHS ]

36:06.083 --> 36:08.083
WHAT DO WE CALL THIS,
THEN?

36:11.166 --> 36:12.625
A MOMENT.

36:27.625 --> 36:29.709
CHARLIE'S PARENTS
ARE IN THERE TOGETHER?

36:29.792 --> 36:31.000
THAT'S NEW, RIGHT?

36:31.083 --> 36:33.000
THE INSURANCE COMPANY
IS ADVISING

36:33.083 --> 36:34.875
CHARLIE BE MOVED
TO A FACILITY.

36:34.959 --> 36:36.917
HIS MOM THINKS
MAYBE THEY'RE RIGHT.

36:37.000 --> 36:38.917
WHAT? WHY?
THAT'S LIKE GIVING UP.

36:39.000 --> 36:41.750
IT'S NOT GIVING UP.
IT'S A PERFECTLY GOOD FACILITY.

36:41.834 --> 36:43.750
WHERE HE'D BE ALL ALONE.
[ SIGHS ]

36:43.834 --> 36:46.000
I'M NOT SURE THAT MATTERS
TO CHARLIE.

36:46.083 --> 36:47.208
IT DOES TO US, BUT --

36:47.291 --> 36:49.208
IT <i>DOES</i> MATTER TO CHARLIE.

36:49.291 --> 36:51.583
HE'S IN THERE.
I-I KNOW IT.

36:51.667 --> 36:54.041
I AGREE WITH YOU.

36:54.125 --> 36:56.583
NO, SERIOUSLY.
I'VE SEEN HIM.

36:56.667 --> 36:58.166
OKAY, WELL, YOU AND DASH

36:58.250 --> 37:00.542
ALSO DIP A LOT
INTO THE PRIVATE STASH, SO...

37:00.625 --> 37:03.125
NURSE JACKSON, LISTEN TO ME.
I'VE TALKED TO HIM.

37:03.208 --> 37:07.125
WHEN I HAD MY FIRST SURGERY, HE
WAS THERE, PLAYING WITH THIS...

37:07.208 --> 37:11.542
LITTLE CREATURE --
AN ORIGAMI THING, AND...

37:11.625 --> 37:14.250
OH, I KNOW THAT COMPLETELY
SOUNDS LIKE I WAS HIGH, BUT...

37:14.333 --> 37:16.542
YOU GOT TO BELIEVE ME.

37:17.625 --> 37:19.542
I DO.

37:19.625 --> 37:21.625
JUST TELL ME
EXACTLY WHAT YOU REMEMBER.

37:24.291 --> 37:26.000
Charlie: HELLO?

37:34.041 --> 37:36.208
HELLO?

37:37.542 --> 37:38.959
HEY.

37:39.041 --> 37:42.333
HEY.

37:42.417 --> 37:43.959
THIS IS WEIRD, RIGHT?

37:44.041 --> 37:46.417
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE.

37:46.500 --> 37:47.834
WHO ARE YOU?

37:49.208 --> 37:50.625
I'M LEO.

37:50.709 --> 37:52.917
I'M CHARLIE.

37:53.000 --> 37:54.959
YOU OKAY?

37:55.041 --> 37:56.583
I MEAN, YOU --
YOU LOOK OKAY.

37:56.667 --> 37:59.458
SO DO YOU.

37:59.542 --> 38:01.208
GUESS WE'VE GOT THAT
GOING FOR US.

38:03.667 --> 38:06.000
SO, UH, WHAT DO WE THINK?

38:06.083 --> 38:09.875
I THINK MAYBE
IT'S WHATEVER WE WANT IT TO BE.

38:13.709 --> 38:15.458
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:15.542 --> 38:18.792
YES!
[ CHUCKLES ]

38:18.875 --> 38:21.333
THEY CAN'T
TAKE CHARLIE AWAY.

38:21.417 --> 38:22.875
HE'S A RED BANDER.

38:22.959 --> 38:24.458
AREN'T THERE STUDIES
THAT SHOW

38:24.542 --> 38:26.041
YOU GET BETTER
BY BEING TOGETHER?

38:26.125 --> 38:29.333
LOOK, I KNOW I CAN'T
PROVE ANYTHING, BUT...

38:29.417 --> 38:31.208
THAT'S GOT TO BE
SOME KIND OF SIGN

38:31.291 --> 38:32.959
THAT HE'S
IN THERE SOMEWHERE.

38:40.792 --> 38:45.291
SINCE WHEN
DO WE GROUP TEXT?

38:45.375 --> 38:47.375
OHH.

38:47.458 --> 38:49.333
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]
Jordi: WHAT'S GOING ON?

38:49.417 --> 38:50.917
WHY ARE WE GATHERING?

38:51.000 --> 38:53.667
I'M NOT SURE, BUT LEO SAID
IT WAS IMPORTANT.

38:53.750 --> 38:55.834
AH, WELL, IF LEO SAYS IT'S
IMPORTANT, IT MUST BE, RIGHT?

38:55.917 --> 38:58.000
♪ TAKE TO THE SKY, OPEN UP YOUR
EYES, AND SEE HOW FAR YOU GET ♪

38:58.083 --> 38:59.834
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

38:59.917 --> 39:02.875
[ BOTTLES CLINK ]

39:02.959 --> 39:04.834
CHARLIE'S
BEING TRANSFERRED.

39:04.917 --> 39:06.917
WAIT.
DOES THIS MEAN I GET A SINGLE?

39:07.000 --> 39:08.709
♪ AND OPEN UP YOUR HEART
AND SEE HOW FAR YOU GET ♪

39:08.792 --> 39:10.208
A QUESTION
FOR ANOTHER TIME.

39:10.291 --> 39:11.834
I THINK
WE SHOULD HAVE A TOAST.

39:11.917 --> 39:13.041
TO CHARLIE.

39:13.125 --> 39:14.667
All: TO CHARLIE.

39:14.750 --> 39:17.583
♪ AND IT'S A BIG OLD WORLD
WE LIVE IN NOW ♪

39:17.667 --> 39:21.375
♪ AND HOW MIGHTY IT CAN BE ♪

39:21.458 --> 39:22.500
WHOA.

39:22.583 --> 39:24.834
THAT WASN'T THERE YESTERDAY.

39:24.917 --> 39:26.375
♪ AND ALL THIS TIME I PICTURED
YOU STANDING NEXT TO ME ♪

39:26.458 --> 39:29.083
YEAH, MAN.
IT JUST CAME OUT OF NOWHERE.

39:29.166 --> 39:32.041
♪ SO WE COULD GO FIND THINGS
WE'VE NEVER SEEN ♪

39:32.125 --> 39:34.083
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

39:34.166 --> 39:36.041
IT'S AMAZING.

40:13.542 --> 40:15.542
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

40:32.917 --> 40:34.375
<i>HEY, NURSE JACKSON,</i>

40:34.458 --> 40:36.291
<i>DID YOU MEAN</i>
<i>TO JUST WRITE MY NAME</i>

40:36.375 --> 40:37.625
<i>ON SOMEONE ELSE'S BLOOD?</i>

40:37.709 --> 40:39.458
<i>THAT'S PROBABLY ILLEGAL, RIGHT?</i>

40:39.542 --> 40:42.125
<i>JUST WONDERING</i>
<i>WHAT THE GAME PLAN IS HERE.</i>

40:42.208 --> 40:44.166
<i>LET ME KNOW.</i>
<i>I'M HERE...</i>

40:44.250 --> 40:47.208
<i>FOR ANOTHER 42 HOURS</i>
<i>AND COUNTING.</i>

40:51.917 --> 40:53.709
[ SIGHS ]
